patriots,

Let me first start by saying wow!!!! It's been a hell of a long few years. After the 2020 election I spent many countless hours wondering how to continue thedonald. After January 6th I was waiting to be jailed for wrong think and more time how to figure out how to continue without the domain name of thedonald.

It's been depressing only stickying Biden failures and the loss of our nation. Going from Trump and winning to the open theft of our freedoms was a somber and harsh adjustment. Thank you all for staying the course, for holding on to hope, and for being a part of something truly meaningful. Despite the challenges we’ve faced, you’ve kept the spirit of this community alive with resilience, loyalty, and an unwavering commitment to Trump.

Looking forward, I’m more certain than ever that our best days are still to come. Together, we have the strength, unity, and drive to keep moving forward not just for ourselves, but for the principles that unite America.

This site will continue we may not have Trump rallies to go to but each day we will be here having our own rally. We'll maintain a high energy environment and I'll have an expectation of everyone to have a great time while here.

I want to thank the posters, the commenters, the donators, the mods, Trump and his team, and everyone who voted for him. This site wouldn't exist without any of you. I do need to single out doggos. He may be the only person who slept less than I these past few years. We owe a lot to him and I'll be forever grateful to him. He's almost as great as a loving little squirrel that helped get Trump over the line.

Four more years of MAGA!!! HELL YEAH!!

posts.title: Grateful
posts.content:
patriots,

Let me first start by saying wow!!!! It's been a hell of a long few years. After the 2020 election I spent many countless hours wondering how to continue thedonald. After January 6th I was waiting to be jailed for wrong think and more time how to figure out how to continue without the domain name of thedonald.

It's been depressing only stickying Biden failures and the loss of our nation. Going from Trump and winning to the open theft of our freedoms was a somber and harsh adjustment. Thank you all for staying the course, for holding on to hope, and for being a part of something truly meaningful. Despite the challenges we’ve faced, you’ve kept the spirit of this community alive with resilience, loyalty, and an unwavering commitment to Trump.

Looking forward, I’m more certain than ever that our best days are still to come. Together, we have the strength, unity, and drive to keep moving forward not just for ourselves, but for the principles that unite America.

This site will continue we may not have Trump rallies to go to but each day we will be here having our own rally. We'll maintain a high energy environment and I'll have an expectation of everyone to have a great time while here.

I want to thank the posters, the commenters, the donators, the mods, Trump and his team, and everyone who voted for him. This site wouldn't exist without any of you. I do need to single out doggos. He may be the only person who slept less than I these past few years. We owe a lot to him and I'll be forever grateful to him. He's almost as great as a loving little squirrel that helped get Trump over the line.

Four more years of MAGA!!! HELL YEAH!!
